Ludwigia hyssopifolia

is a pantropical species (
Raven 1963
; 
Zardini & Raven 1997
). In 
Brazil
, it is distributed in the North (AC, AM, PA, RO, 
RR
), Northeast (AL, BA, 
PE
), Central-West (MS, 
MT
), Southeast (MG, 
SP
) and South (
PR
) regions, associated with Amazon, Atlantic Rainforest and Pantanal phytogeographic domains (Vieira 2015).
